text: I'm now certain who sent that transmission to the Federation. Those threats must have come from the Mawkin's leader, {c1}Raven Beak{c0}. His desire to rule the galaxy using the power of the Metroids is well known in the Federation.
I suspect this is why his systems locked the gate to his lair as we approached. Raven Beak won't allow anyone to enter without a living Metroid. But I have a solution.

Federation records show that the Mawkin stored samples of {c1}Metroid DNA{c0} in each of the regions of ZDR for safekeeping. If you were to inject yourself with them and then present yourself to his systems, they would recognize you as a Metroid.
{c1}Locate the DNA samples and inject yourself with them, no matter the cost.{c0}|Any objections, Lady?
Samus, what happened to your abilities?
You lost them after injecting yourself with Metroid DNA?
Well... That will certainly make this more difficult. But our only choice is to proceed anyways.
Try to collect anything that could be useful. ZDR seems to be full of {c1}Chozo technology{c0}, so you should be able to find something compatible with your suit.

By the way, I'm able to retrieve some information about ZDR while uploaded to these stations, so I've located the next DNA sample. It's at the {c3}western edge{c0} of this region. Go collect it.|Any objections, Lady?
I've made an unfortunate discovery. Most of the transportation networks on ZDR have been disabled. I'm investigating the cause, but for now, you'll just have to make use of the ones that still work.
Thankfully, I've located a {c1}functioning transport{c0} next to this region's DNA sample.
Lady, continue what you've been doing. We need that Metroid DNA.
It seems like you've lost your abilities again. There's only one thing this could mean...
Samus, I think the injections are mutating your body too dramatically for your suit. It can't support both your abilities and you. You'll just have to recollect them each time.
I've located this region's DNA sample. It's {c3}southeast of here{c0}. Re-equip yourself again and then collect it.|Any objections, Lady?

It seems Raven Beak has replicated the Federation's {c1}E.M.M.I. robots{c0}. The one in Artaria didn't pose too much trouble, but the one you just faced seemed to be significantly enhanced. It's a good thing you were trained on how to dispatch a rogue E.M.M.I.

I've located the next DNA sample. It's deep underwater, at the {c3}southeast edge{c0} of the region. You don't have the {c1}Gravity Suit{c0} anymore, so be prepared to use other abilities to proceed. Let's hope the water won't be too much trouble until you find it again.
Both the DNA sample and a working transport are nearby.|I'm worried, though.
The next region is a tightly sealed fortress. Records show it's a Mawkin training ground, but there have been {c1}no signs of activity{c0} since we arrived.
Don't you find that strange? Something isn't right about this, Lady. Retrieve the DNA sample from within and leave as quickly as possible.

So Raven Beak's threats weren't empty, after all... he really did capture|{c1}X parasites{c0}. But I don't understand why the facility made no attempt to contain the X once you entered. It's as if it let them escape purposefully...

In any case, we don't know if the X of ZDR are stronger than the ones on the B.S.L., so proceed with extreme caution.|I've located the next sample of DNA at the {c3}northeast edge{c0} of this region. Continue your mission, Lady.
I've been monitoring the transportation networks of ZDR closely, and I caught something. After you took that teleporter, I detected a signal...
That signal came from {c1}Raven Beak's lair{c0}. We can now confirm that the transportation networks are being controlled by him.

But why is he doing this? Think about it. When you left Elun, the transport was redirected to bring you to a new region. If Raven Beak wanted to stop you, why would he bring you closer to the next DNA?
Our efforts must be furthering his plans... this can only mean one thing. An ordinary Metroid is not enough for Raven Beak.|{c1}He wants to control the strongest Metroid of all... Samus Aran.{c0}
Your power has grown far beyond what we could have expected. You would make him unstoppable. When the time comes, you must be strong enough to defeat him.
For now, you have to continue your mission. The next DNA sample can be found at the {c3}north edge{c0} of this region. Don't let anything stop you.|Any objections, Lady?
I think we now have enough data to confirm the strength of the X of ZDR. They seem to be much more powerful than those you faced on the B.S.L.
You are only able to overpower them because of your growing Metroid power. In the state you were in when we arrived on ZDR, you would have had almost no chance of survival.
I wonder...
Wait... Hold on... I'm detecting an {c1}extremely powerful X{c0} nearby. It seems to be attacking a thermal generator that's powering much of the planet.
Lady, you must stop it. If that generator is damaged too severely, it could set off a chain reaction powerful enough to destroy ZDR.
We have unlocked almost all of your Metroid potential. There's only one more DNA sample to collect.
....................||Hold on... these readings from your suit... your body can't take much more of this.
You knew about it, didn't you? You knew that you would become {c1}more Metroid than human{c0}...

If you take this last injection, the balance between your Metroid and human DNA will become unstable... any defensive instinct could disturb it and transform you fully into a Metroid.|Are you sure you want to continue?
Very well... the last sample is {c3}close by{c0}, as well as a teleportal to Raven Beak's lair. I will likely lose contact with you once you are inside.|Finish your mission, Lady.

hints.text: How are you reading this? This text should never be visible in-game, so something's gone terribly wrong.|Please contact {c1}may_berry{c0} on Discord.

text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_01: Good work, Samus. You have collected all the Metroid DNA and are now strong enough to face Raven Beak.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_02: Of course, you know who I really am.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_03: Do you really think that even now, you could be stronger than me?
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_04: You sheepishly followed the orders given to you by your commanding officer.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_05: You risked your life time after time by injecting yourself with Metroid DNA, all because you were told to.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_06: Without my help, you never would have reached the DNA samples and become as strong as you are now.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_07: I have been guiding you all along. Every place you found yourself in, you were in because of me.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_08: You are weak on your own.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_09: You have neither the will nor the ability to realize your own potential.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_10: Even now, you continue to stand there, quietly listening to every word I say.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_11: No matter how much your physical strength grows, your loyalty to others will forever shackle you.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_13: You have forfeited the right to your own power.
text_patches.DIAG_ADAM_FINAL_PAGE_14: Very well. Finally face me, then...
text_patches.CAPTION_HYPERMETROIDNIZATIONEVENT_PAGE_0: Did you truly believe you could defeat me? You overestimate yourself.
The energy contained within you is enough to make anyone who wields it into a ruler.
You are not worthy of such a title.
I will do something that you never could.
I will change this galaxy with my own two hands.
If only you could live to see it.
